Makes 12 Ingredients: 500 g Snowflake Savoury Muffin Easymix 1 extra-large egg 125 ml ( cup) cooking oil 375 ml (1 cups) milk 150 g spinach 1 ml cayenne pepper 250 ml (100 g) grated Cheddar cheese &nbsp; Method Steam spinach until wilted. Drain, chop coarsely and set aside. Preheat oven to 180 C. Place easymix into a mixing bowl. Add cayenne pepper, cheese and spinach. Whisk egg, oil and milk before adding to dry ingredients. Mix lightly with a spoon until just combined. Do not overmix. Spoon mixture into a well-greased muffin pan. Bake for about 20 minutes or until golden brown. Turn out onto a wire rack to cool. &nbsp; Healthy bake trick Swap butter, margarine or vegetable shortening for heart-healthy oils, such as olive oil and canola oil. &nbsp;